112
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:41,640
I'm actually hungry.

113
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:45,520
What was I saying?

114
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:48,560
I made a foreign business deal.

115
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:50,960
Look at you showing off.

116
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:51,880
Foreign business, huh?

117
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:52,880
How did you do it?

118
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:54,560
Did you use gestures?

119
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:56,000
Speaking in sign language?

120
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:59,200
They're all Chinese. Why would I use sign language?

121
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:01,080
If they're all Chinese,

122
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:02,740
how is that foreign business?

123
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:05,920
I earned foreign money.

124
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:07,140
Foreign money?

125
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:09,840
Twenty euros.

126
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:11,360
Euros.

127
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:13,080
What does it look like? Let me see.

128
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:13,740
Where is it?

129
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:16,560
I've already exchanged it for yuan.

130
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:18,210
How much did you get?

131
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:20,600
100 yuan.

132
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:22,520
Wait, you've been talking all this time

133
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:24,120
and only sold one item?

134
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:27,240
Hurry back to your stall.

135
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:29,300
We still need to bail out Brother Cui.

136
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,890
I'm trying to teach you that

137
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:33,520
business requires an international perspective.

138
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:35,780
Why aren't you interested in new things?

139
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:37,520
Not interested.

140
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:40,280
I just want to get Brother Cui back quickly.

141
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:40,960
That's what I'm interested in.

142
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:41,440
Now hurry up.

143
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:42,240
Hurry!

144
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,240
Quick!

145
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,240
Down jackets!

146
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,400
Are we still playing?

147
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:50,920
Hey.

148
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:52,850
Is it fun always winning like this?

149
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:00,000
If only my life

150
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:02,240
could always be winning like this.

151
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:03,490
Unfortunately.

152
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:05,600
Right now

153
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,730
I've probably hit rock bottom.

154
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:09,730
Don't worry.

155
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:12,240
People who think they've hit rock bottom

156
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:13,480
usually haven't yet.

157
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:16,480
There's an even deeper bottom waiting for you.

158
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:18,520
I'm locked up with you

159
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,210
and that's not rock bottom?

160
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:21,800
Sure thing.

161
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:25,240
Auntie,

162
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:27,770
Xiaoxue's dog bit my turtle and made it bleed.

163
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,400
Did it die?

164
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:31,080
No, but it's badly injured.

165
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:32,920
Very serious. I bandaged it up.

166
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:34,640
When is Uncle coming back?

167
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:36,200
If he doesn't come back soon to weld the dog cage,

168
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:38,200
my turtle won't survive three days.

169
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:40,640
What a day.

170
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:50,560
Hey.

171
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:52,960
The motorcycle and nesting dolls are all put away.

172
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,480
How are you doing over there?

173
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:55,280
Pretty good.

174
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:56,080
Well,

175
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,600
give those four nesting dolls

176
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,720
to the children.

177
00:07:58,840 --> 00:08:00,360
Oh my goodness, Xiaozhi is still so young.

178
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:01,820
Can he even play with them?

179
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,400
When are you coming back?

180
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,040
Soon.

181
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:06,120
I need to go for a business meeting.

182
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:06,850
You carry on.

183
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:07,960
Hanging up,

184
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,480
okay?

185
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,960
You lie so easily.

186
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:17,820
I'm very busy with business here.

187
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:20,680
What am I supposed to tell my wife?

188
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:21,920
That I've been locked up

189
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,120
because of a honey trap?

190
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,280
If you have a wife,

191
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:26,200
why are you out here fooling around?

192
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:27,680
Who's fooling around?

193
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:31,600
Hello.

194
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:35,720
My two good friends,

195
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:37,890
are you comfortable staying here?

196
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:41,400
You're here.

197
00:08:44,039 --> 00:08:46,680
Just a few more hours until it's time.

198
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:49,280
Are you confident about this?

199
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:50,480
Absolutely.

200
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:53,360
Why don't we make a call to confirm?

201
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:55,080
No need. Just wait.

202
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:57,020
I was just telling Brother Cui

203
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:58,520
that such a nice girl like you,

204
00:08:58,520 --> 00:09:00,050
why would you be doing this?

205
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:00,880
Listen to me.

206
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:02,540
Let's change our profession.

207
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:10,520
You're lecturing me.

208
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:16,440
Then let me lecture you too.

209
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:20,480
In the future, when good opportunities fall from the sky,

210
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:22,140
especially beautiful women,

211
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:24,080
you'd better think twice.

212
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,680
Otherwise,

213
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:27,560
you'll get burned again.

214
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:29,680
What do you mean?

215
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:32,360
What do I mean?

216
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:36,890
There's no mirror in this pool hall

217
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:39,040
so you can't see yourself.

218
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:41,160
The way you talk is just too-

219
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:42,360
Shut up.

220
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,120
In a year

221
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:51,760
I deal with hundreds of clients.

222
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:55,040
But someone as decent

223
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:57,130
and straightforward as you

224
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:59,880
I don't meet even one all year.

225
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:02,720
But there's something I'm confused about.

226
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,640
How could someone as smart

227
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:06,000
and cultured as you

228
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:08,440
be doing business

229
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:09,960
with those two guys?

230
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:13,080
If they can't gather 20,000

231
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:16,200
what do you plan to do?

232
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:18,240
Just kill me then.

233
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:26,760
We wouldn't dare.

234
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:27,800
If you don't dare, then get out.

235
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:30,460
We'll deal with that if they can't get the money.

236
00:10:30,520 --> 00:10:31,720
Your personality

237
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:33,920
I really like it.

238
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,000
If the money's not enough

239
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:41,880
you'll be in trouble.

240
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,800
If you've got the guts, kill me.

241
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:49,240
You said it yourself.

242
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:52,240
Do you dare?

243
00:10:57,760 --> 00:10:58,600
Just try it.

244
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:27,680
Why do you think she doesn't dare to kill you

245
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:28,810
but dares to kill me?

246
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:30,160
Thirty years ago,

247
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:32,000
my teacher said something.

248
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:33,640
What was it?

249
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:35,890
You're not serious enough.

250
00:11:36,520 --> 00:11:38,580
What does 'not serious enough' mean?

251
00:11:39,040 --> 00:11:40,760
Anyway, my teacher said the same about me.

252
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:42,040
I have a friend outside

253
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:43,940
who's not serious either.

254
00:11:44,680 --> 00:11:47,720
You two would definitely get along well if you met.

255
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:54,240
Direct from

256
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,240
Direct from

257
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:58,760
Direct from factory!

258
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:03,160
You shout, I can't.

259
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:06,760
We still need 2,300.

260
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:09,480
How many hours left?

261
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:10,720
100 yuan per item, only one hour left.

262
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:12,000
Hurry up and sell. Come on!

263
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,640
Come get your down jackets!

264
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:14,760
Clearance sale!

265
00:12:14,760 --> 00:12:16,440
Clearance sale! Down jackets!

266
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:17,720
100 yuan each!

267
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:18,960
100 yuan each! Come take a look!

268
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:20,520
Super thick and warm!

269
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,240
100 yuan each!

270
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:23,840
Just 100! Come see!

271
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:24,800
Direct from factory!

272
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:25,880
100 yuan each!

273
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,840
How are these down jackets from this morning?

274
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:29,400
Not bad.

275
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:31,320
I've brought my friend here.

276
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,320
My friend says

277
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:33,760
if you can lower the price,

278
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:35,420
he'll take as many as you have.

279
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:37,080
How much cheaper do you want?

280
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:38,320
Not a penny less.

281
00:12:38,880 --> 00:12:40,000
Are you stupid?

282
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:41,960
We're selling them for 100 yuan.

283
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:43,040
Right.

284
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:43,920
If we weren't trying to

285
00:12:43,920 --> 00:12:45,040
get our friend back...

286
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:45,800
No, wait.

287
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:46,840
What nonsense are you talking?

288
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:47,440
Nonsense!

289
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:48,720
Five yuan off each,

290
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:49,760
